AreaAggregateAreaID.description: The area within which the address aggregate is to be found.

AreaAggregateEffect.description: Subnets subsumed by ranges either trigger the advertisement of the indicated aggregate (advertiseMatching) or result in the subnet's not being advertised at all outside the area.

AreaAggregateExtRouteTag.description: External route tag to be included in NSSA (type-7) LSAs.

AreaAggregateLsdbType.description: The type of the address aggregate.  This field specifies the Lsdb type that this address aggregate applies to.

AreaAggregateMask.description: The subnet mask that pertains to the net or subnet.

AreaAggregateNet.description: The IP address of the net or subnet indicated by the range.
